gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 122, 76ers 119
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers outlast the 76ers, in overtime, 122-119.  Darius Garland led the way with 32 points, five rebounds and eight assists for the Cavaliers, while Jarrett Allen added 26 points and 13 rebounds in the victory. Joel Embiid (32 points, 13 rebounds, five assists, five blocks) and Tyrese Maxey (30 points, six assists) combined for 62 points in the losing effort. The Cavaliers have won their 4th consecutive game and improve to  8-6, 2-1 in IST play, while the 76ers fall to 10-4, 2-2 in IST play.
